<DOC><DOCNO> AP900502-0246 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-05-02-90 1522EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r f BC-Europe-Utilities     05-02 0142</FIRST><SECOND>BC-Europe-Utilities,0151</SECOND><HEAD>EC Plans To Expand Gas, Electricity Networks</HEAD><DATELINE>BRUSSELS, Belgium (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   The European Community Commission saidWednesday it plans to spend $363 million to improve and expandnatural gas and electricity infrastructures in key regions.   EC Regional Affairs Commissioner Bruce Millan said thethree-year plan would give special priority to infrastructureprojects that could promote intra-European energy trade.   The projects to be financed under the European Community programinclude:   _Building receiving facilities and transmission networks tointroduce natural gas into Portugal and Greece.   _Establishing a connection between gas transmission networks inIreland and Britain.   _Including the French island of Corsica in a possible futureconnection of gas transmission networks between the Italianmainland and the Italian island of Sardinia.   _Forming a gas transmission network between Portugal and Spain.   _Establishing a connection between electricity distributionnetworks in Italy and Greece.</TEXT></DOC>